==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mote
<hw>Mote</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Moot</er>, a meeting.]</ety>
<mark>[Obs., except in a few combinations or phrases.]</mark>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A meeting of persons for discussion; <as>as, a
ward<ex>mote</ex> in the city of London</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A body of persons who meet for discussion, esp.
about the management of affairs; <as>as, a
folk<ex>mote</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A place of meeting for discussion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mote bell</b></col>, <cd>the bell rung to summon to a
<ex>mote</ex>.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mote</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Mote
<hw>Mote</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The flourish sounded on a horn by a
huntsman. See <er>Mot</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 3, and <er>Mort</er>.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mote</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Mote
<hw>Mote</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>mot</ets>, AS.
<ets>mot</ets>.]</ety> <def>A small particle, as of floating dust;
anything proverbially small; a speck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The little <qex>motes</qex> in the sun do ever stir, though there
be no wind.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We are <qex>motes</qex> in the midst of generations.</q>
<rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moted</ent>⟦br⟧
